This paper is likely to belong to the category of computer security (cs.CR) because it presents a black-box adversarial attack algorithm that aims to evade machine learning models. Additionally, it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) because it deals with the optimization of gradient estimation and the evasion of machine learning models trained on image datasets.
